<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<subsection xml:id="course_description" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Course Description</title>
  <p>
    This course provides a comprehensive study of trigonometric concepts, including the solution of right triangles, reduction formulas, functions of multiple angles, and trigonometric equations. We will also explore inverse trigonometric functions and their applications, as well as the connections between trigonometry and complex numbers. 
  </p>
  <p>
Trigonometry plays a fundamental role in mathematics, engineering, physics, and many other disciplines. Through a combination of theory, problem-solving, and practical applications, you will develop a strong foundation that will support further study and problem-solving in a variety of fields.
  </p>
</subsection>
